# Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
# Only the Google Maps keys are documented here; other public client IDs and
# Firebase config live in app.json (they are public by design).
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Google Maps keys — injected into the Expo config by app.config.js so they are
# NEVER committed to the repo. Create TWO separate, restricted keys in the
# Google Cloud Console (do not reuse one key for both):
#
# 1) Places + Geocoding (client web calls: Place Autocomplete/Details, Geocoding)
#    Cloud Console → API restriction: "Places API" + "Geocoding API" only.
#    Application restriction: none possible for mobile web calls — protect with
#    per-key quotas + billing alerts. NOTE: EXPO_PUBLIC_* is inlined into the app
#    bundle, so this key still ships in the app; the API restriction + quotas
#    are what limit abuse. (A server-side proxy would remove it from the client.)
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=

# 2) Native Google Maps SDK on Android (iOS uses Apple Maps and needs no key).
#    Cloud Console → API restriction: "Maps SDK for Android" only.
#    Application restriction: Android apps → package `com.bondvibe.app` + the
#    app's SHA-1 fingerprint (from `eas credentials` / Firebase / Play Console).
GOOGLE_MAPS_ANDROID_API_KEY=
